Greetings, brothers and sisters.

00:00:17.829 --> 00:00:21.829
Today's session will begin with a music video presentation

00:00:21.829 --> 00:00:25.829
that reminds us of our privilege and responsibility

00:00:25.829 --> 00:00:27.829
to help others develop faith.

00:00:27.829 --> 00:00:30.829
Please enjoy the presentation.

00:00:58.409 --> 00:10:31.250
Welcome back to our Powerful by Faith Regional Convention.

00:10:31.250 --> 00:10:34.250
During this session and the next one,

00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:37.250
you will hear the talks listed under the Saturday Heading

00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:39.250
of your printed program.

00:10:39.250 --> 00:10:44.529
The scripture theme for today's program is taken from Jude

00:10:44.529 --> 00:10:50.529
3, where we are told to put up a hard fight for the faith.

00:10:50.529 --> 00:10:54.529
We'll see how we can demonstrate our faith regardless of our

00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:59.529
circumstances, and we'll see how we can help others to build faith.

00:10:59.529 --> 00:11:05.129
Now, let's share in singing song number 57, entitled,

00:11:05.129 --> 00:11:08.129
preaching to all sorts of people.

00:11:08.129 --> 00:13:54.340
Again, that song number 57, in your ministry,

00:13:54.340 --> 00:13:59.340
do you meet some who seem unlikely to respond favorably?

00:13:59.340 --> 00:14:02.340
Are you prepared to help them?

00:14:02.340 --> 00:14:06.340
As we will see in our first symposium of this session,

00:14:06.340 --> 00:14:10.340
our attitude toward others can affect how we give a witness

00:14:10.340 --> 00:14:13.340
and how people might respond.

00:14:14.340 --> 00:14:18.970
Each speaker will introduce the one to follow.

00:14:18.970 --> 00:14:21.970
Please give your attention to Brother Ronald Curson,

00:14:21.970 --> 00:14:23.970
a helper to the teaching committee.

00:14:23.970 --> 00:14:25.970
He will begin with a theme.

00:14:25.970 --> 00:14:29.970
Remember, faithless people can acquire faith.

00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:31.970
The Ninevites.

00:14:31.970 --> 00:14:41.909
Impossible. It will never happen.

00:14:41.909 --> 00:14:43.909
Not in a million years.

00:14:43.909 --> 00:14:47.909
Have you ever thought that way about someone coming into the truth?

00:14:47.909 --> 00:14:51.909
Well, that might be our limited view of a person.

00:14:51.909 --> 00:14:54.909
But how does Jehovah view him or her?

00:14:54.909 --> 00:14:59.909
And what is his view of all humans, even faithless ones?

00:14:59.909 --> 00:15:06.909
Notice his limitless view at 1 Timothy, chapter 2 and verse 4.

00:15:06.909 --> 00:15:11.909
There it says, whose will is that all sorts of people should be saved

00:15:11.909 --> 00:15:15.909
and come to an accurate knowledge of truth.

00:15:15.909 --> 00:15:18.909
So what is Jehovah's desire?

00:15:18.909 --> 00:15:21.909
It's his will that all hear the message

00:15:21.909 --> 00:15:25.909
and be allowed to make changes and be saved.

00:15:25.909 --> 00:15:27.909
Now to us that might be impossible,

00:15:27.909 --> 00:15:30.909
but we know with God all things are possible.

00:15:30.909 --> 00:15:35.909
He can stir the heart and he can motivate anyone.

00:15:35.909 --> 00:15:39.909
While it's true that faith is not the possession of all people,

00:15:39.909 --> 00:15:43.909
it is the possession of millions around the world.

00:15:43.909 --> 00:15:47.909
And it can be for those who choose to acquire it.

00:15:47.909 --> 00:15:51.909
We know the Bible contains many examples of men and women

00:15:51.909 --> 00:15:55.909
who at one time lacked faith, but later acquired it.

00:15:55.909 --> 00:15:57.909
And the same is true today.

00:15:57.909 --> 00:15:59.909
It's not impossible.

00:15:59.909 --> 00:16:03.909
This symposium will help us to remember this fact.

00:16:03.909 --> 00:16:09.909
Faithless people can acquire faith if we have Jehovah's view

00:16:09.909 --> 00:16:14.909
of all sorts of people to hear God's word and make adjustments.

00:16:14.909 --> 00:16:19.909
We will discuss four groups of people in this symposium,

00:16:19.909 --> 00:16:24.909
the Ninevites, Jesus' fleshly brothers, prominent ones,

00:16:24.909 --> 00:16:26.909
and non-religious people.

00:16:26.909 --> 00:16:29.909
And in each one of these symposium talks,

00:16:29.909 --> 00:16:32.909
we will consider what help former unbelievers

00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:36.909
to acquire faith and what we can learn.

00:16:36.909 --> 00:16:40.909
First, let's consider the example of the Ninevites.

00:16:40.909 --> 00:16:43.909
As you recall, they are Assyrians or were Assyrians

00:16:43.909 --> 00:16:46.909
who lived in the capital city of Nineveh,

00:16:46.909 --> 00:16:48.909
and it was founded by Nimrod.

00:16:48.909 --> 00:16:51.909
It was referred to as the city of bloodshed.

00:16:51.909 --> 00:16:53.909
With that history and backdrop,

00:16:53.909 --> 00:16:56.909
we can imagine what the people were like.

00:16:56.909 --> 00:16:59.909
They worship God's of war.

00:16:59.909 --> 00:17:01.909
War was their religion.

00:17:01.909 --> 00:17:04.910
Yes, they were aggressive, they were violent people,

00:17:04.910 --> 00:17:09.910
and they took pleasure in sadistically torturing their captives.

00:17:09.910 --> 00:17:13.910
Well, their reputation was known by all the surrounding nations,

00:17:13.910 --> 00:17:15.910
including God's people.

00:17:15.910 --> 00:17:18.910
So that's why Jehovah sent his prophet Jonah

00:17:18.910 --> 00:17:21.910
to go there and proclaim their destruction.

00:17:21.910 --> 00:17:24.910
As we noticed this first video,

00:17:24.910 --> 00:17:27.910
imagine how Jonah must have felt going into Nineveh,

00:17:27.910 --> 00:17:31.910
going through the streets and observing the people of Nineveh,

00:17:31.910 --> 00:17:33.910
contemplating his warning message.

00:17:33.910 --> 00:18:49.710
How did Jonah view his assignment?

00:18:49.710 --> 00:18:52.710
Well, at this time, he did not have Jehovah's view.

00:18:52.710 --> 00:18:54.710
He was afraid of the Ninevites,

00:18:54.710 --> 00:18:56.710
maybe what they thought of him,

00:18:56.710 --> 00:18:59.710
or what they would do once they heard his message.

00:18:59.710 --> 00:19:01.710
Well, Jonah was human.

00:19:01.710 --> 00:19:03.710
He had feelings like ours.

00:19:03.710 --> 00:19:07.710
A human tendency is to judge people on what we see

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:09.710
or what we hear about them.

00:19:09.710 --> 00:19:11.710
If you were alive then,

00:19:11.710 --> 00:19:15.710
and Jehovah gave you this assignment instead of Jonah,

00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:17.710
how might you have reacted?

00:19:17.710 --> 00:19:19.710
Would you have thought about the Ninevites

00:19:19.710 --> 00:19:22.710
and their cruelty and their wickedness and say,

00:19:22.710 --> 00:19:26.710
they can't change or would you feel it's impossible?

00:19:26.710 --> 00:19:29.710
It'll never happen, not in a million years.

00:19:29.710 --> 00:19:31.710
Well, that's how Jonah felt.

00:19:31.710 --> 00:19:35.710
But Jehovah corrected his view of his assignment

00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:37.710
as well as the people.

00:19:37.710 --> 00:19:40.710
And he took that message

00:19:40.710 --> 00:19:43.710
and that counsel from Jehovah to heart.

00:19:43.710 --> 00:19:47.710
He proclaimed the message to the people of Ninevah.

00:19:47.710 --> 00:19:50.710
He certainly got the Ninevites attention,

00:19:50.710 --> 00:19:52.710
but he might have thought to himself,

00:19:52.710 --> 00:19:54.710
well, this is the end for me.

00:19:54.710 --> 00:19:56.710
But how did they respond?

00:19:56.710 --> 00:20:02.890
Notice, Jonah chapter three and verse five.

00:20:02.890 --> 00:20:06.890
It says, and the men of Ninevah put faith in God.

00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:09.890
So this surprise even Jonah himself,

00:20:09.890 --> 00:20:12.890
the king made a proclamation for all the people

00:20:12.890 --> 00:20:15.890
of what they should do to demonstrate their faith.

00:20:15.890 --> 00:20:17.890
Notice verse eight.

00:20:17.890 --> 00:20:19.890
It says, let them be covered with sackcloth,

00:20:19.890 --> 00:20:21.890
both man and beast,

00:20:21.890 --> 00:20:24.890
and let them call out earnestly to God,

00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:26.890
and turn from their evil ways

00:20:26.890 --> 00:20:28.890
and from the violence they practice.

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:30.890
Who knows whether the true God

00:20:30.890 --> 00:20:33.890
may reconsider what he intends to do

00:20:33.890 --> 00:20:35.890
and turn from his burning anger

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:39.890
so that we may not perish?

00:20:39.890 --> 00:20:44.890
What helped the Ninevites to change to acquire faith?

00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:48.890
It was a direct result of Jonah accomplishing his assignment,

00:20:48.890 --> 00:20:52.890
boldly preaching God's message.

00:20:52.890 --> 00:20:54.890
They were given the opportunity to change

00:20:54.890 --> 00:20:58.890
and to Jonah's surprise, they did.

00:20:58.890 --> 00:21:00.890
But Jonah had to make changes too.

00:21:00.890 --> 00:21:03.890
He had to take his limited view of his assignment

00:21:03.890 --> 00:21:06.890
and the people and change it to the limitless view

00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:09.890
that Jehovah had, that people can change

00:21:09.890 --> 00:21:12.890
and Jehovah can stir their hearts.

00:21:12.890 --> 00:21:15.890
And Jonah had to look at himself

00:21:15.890 --> 00:21:17.890
and relook at his assignment.

00:21:17.890 --> 00:21:20.890
He was not the judge, he was not the jury,

00:21:20.890 --> 00:21:23.890
he was a messenger.

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:26.890
Having Jehovah's view changes everything.

00:21:26.890 --> 00:21:28.890
How we view others, how we view ourselves,

00:21:28.890 --> 00:21:31.890
how we view our assignments today.

00:21:31.890 --> 00:21:34.890
We are ministers who have a message.

00:21:34.890 --> 00:21:37.890
We are not the judges.

00:21:37.890 --> 00:21:39.890
Well, Jehovah is the judge.

00:21:39.890 --> 00:21:41.890
And how did he judge the Ninevites

00:21:41.890 --> 00:21:45.890
worthy of being saved and have his mercy?

00:21:45.890 --> 00:21:51.890
Notice, Jonah, chapter 3, and their in verse 10.

00:21:51.890 --> 00:21:54.890
It says, when the true God saw what they did

00:21:54.890 --> 00:21:57.890
and how they had turned back from their evil ways,

00:21:57.890 --> 00:22:01.890
he reconsidered the calamity that he said he would bring on them.

00:22:01.890 --> 00:22:05.890
And he did not bring it.

00:22:05.890 --> 00:22:10.140
In the following video, notice the changes

00:22:10.140 --> 00:22:13.140
that the Ninevites made and how they benefited.

00:22:13.140 --> 00:23:01.950
Are you Jonah?

00:23:01.950 --> 00:23:03.950
I am.

00:23:03.950 --> 00:23:04.950
Thank you.

00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:15.210
Well, the Ninevites certainly changed

00:23:15.210 --> 00:23:18.210
from the first video that we watched.

00:23:18.210 --> 00:23:20.210
Changes they made on the inside,

00:23:20.210 --> 00:23:23.210
allowed them to make changes on the outside,

00:23:23.210 --> 00:23:25.210
how they viewed their fellow Ninevites

00:23:25.210 --> 00:23:27.210
and how they treated them.

00:23:27.210 --> 00:23:30.210
And their dispositions changed from gloomy,

00:23:30.210 --> 00:23:34.210
unhappy faces to smiling, happy ones.

00:23:34.210 --> 00:23:37.210
They were appreciative of Jonah's warning message

00:23:37.210 --> 00:23:40.210
as well as Jehovah's mercy.

00:23:40.210 --> 00:23:43.210
What's the lesson for us?

00:23:43.210 --> 00:23:45.210
The same lesson that Jonah learned.

00:23:45.210 --> 00:23:49.210
We need to show compassion as Jehovah does.

00:23:49.210 --> 00:23:52.210
This means more than just noticing that someone needs help,

00:23:52.210 --> 00:23:55.210
but taking the time and having the desire

00:23:55.210 --> 00:23:59.210
to try to relieve that pain, help them.

00:23:59.210 --> 00:24:03.210
How can we imitate Jehovah's compassion today?

00:24:03.210 --> 00:24:06.210
It's by putting compassion into action.

00:24:06.210 --> 00:24:09.210
And we do this by our preaching.

00:24:09.210 --> 00:24:11.210
And we do this to all persons,

00:24:11.210 --> 00:24:14.210
giving them an opportunity to change

00:24:14.210 --> 00:24:16.210
and not be judgmental.

00:24:16.210 --> 00:24:18.210
By viewing them as potential sheep

00:24:18.210 --> 00:24:22.210
as our future brother or sister.

00:24:22.210 --> 00:24:24.210
Like the Ninevites,

00:24:24.210 --> 00:24:26.210
many today are taught wrong beliefs

00:24:26.210 --> 00:24:28.210
and attitudes from childhood.

00:24:28.210 --> 00:24:30.210
And it may be difficult to change,

00:24:30.210 --> 00:24:33.210
but not impossible.

00:24:33.210 --> 00:24:35.210
What can help them change?

00:24:35.210 --> 00:24:39.210
Hebrews 4.12 says the word of God can help.

00:24:39.210 --> 00:24:44.210
The word of God is alive and exerts power.

00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:46.210
Many of us are living proof

00:24:46.210 --> 00:24:49.210
of the Bible's power to change us.

00:24:49.210 --> 00:24:51.210
Before learning the truth,

00:24:51.210 --> 00:24:55.210
some of us might have been violent, immoral, faithless.

00:24:55.210 --> 00:24:57.210
But as the Apostle Paul says,

00:24:57.210 --> 00:25:00.210
that is what some of you were.

00:25:00.210 --> 00:25:02.210
They change back then.

00:25:02.210 --> 00:25:04.210
People are changing today.

00:25:04.210 --> 00:25:06.210
With the help of God's Word

00:25:06.210 --> 00:25:07.210
and His Holy Spirit,

00:25:07.210 --> 00:25:10.210
we can help others change.

00:25:10.210 --> 00:25:12.210
And we cannot read hearts.

00:25:12.210 --> 00:25:14.210
But we know that Jehovah can.

00:25:14.210 --> 00:25:18.210
And he can stir the heart, motivate anyone.

00:25:19.210 --> 00:25:21.210
What can we do in the meantime?

00:25:21.210 --> 00:25:27.210
We can remember to follow what Romans chapter 10 and verse 16 says.

00:25:27.210 --> 00:25:30.210
Our assignment is to be a messenger.

00:25:30.210 --> 00:25:32.210
Notice verse 16.

00:25:32.210 --> 00:25:34.210
Nevertheless,

00:25:34.210 --> 00:25:36.210
they did not all obey the good news.

00:25:36.210 --> 00:25:38.210
For Isaiah says,

00:25:38.210 --> 00:25:41.210
Jehovah, who has put faith in the thing heard from us?

00:25:41.210 --> 00:25:44.210
So faith follows the thing heard.

00:25:45.210 --> 00:25:48.210
In turn, what is heard is through the word about Christ.

00:25:48.210 --> 00:25:51.210
Faith follows the things heard.

00:25:51.210 --> 00:25:54.210
What motivated the Ninevice to change?

00:25:54.210 --> 00:25:57.210
It was only after they heard Jonas' warning message.

00:25:57.210 --> 00:26:01.210
It is our hope and prayer that many will put faith in God

00:26:01.210 --> 00:26:04.210
because of the warning message that we give.

00:26:04.210 --> 00:26:09.210
So may we be like Jonah, be compassionate, but bold,

00:26:09.210 --> 00:26:11.210
and preaching the good news to all.

00:26:11.210 --> 00:26:15.210
Who knows, faith may follow the things heard.

00:26:15.210 --> 00:26:18.210
Remember, it is possible.

00:26:18.210 --> 00:26:23.210
Faithless people can acquire faith.

00:26:23.210 --> 00:26:26.210
Brother Mark Sanderson, a member of the governing body,

00:26:26.210 --> 00:26:29.210
will now consider the next part of this symposium.

00:26:29.210 --> 00:26:32.210
Remember, faithless people can acquire faith.

00:26:32.210 --> 00:26:34.210
Jesus, fleshly brothers.

00:26:34.210 --> 00:26:46.059
