00:26:46.059 --> 00:26:50.059
I think most of us do, and we're not alone.

00:26:50.059 --> 00:26:54.059
Even our Lord Jesus had that same circumstance.

00:26:54.059 --> 00:26:59.059
Even though his half-brothers knew about the miracles he was performing,

00:26:59.059 --> 00:27:06.059
the Bible says that they were not expressing faith in Jesus as the Messiah.

00:27:06.059 --> 00:27:12.059
Well, it was so bad, can you imagine, that when Jesus was being put to death,

00:27:12.059 --> 00:27:15.059
it appears that his brothers were not there.

00:27:15.059 --> 00:27:19.059
Remember the account where Jesus was on the torture stake,

00:27:19.059 --> 00:27:23.059
and he looked down at the disciple and asked him, basically,

00:27:23.059 --> 00:27:26.059
to become responsible for his mother.

00:27:26.059 --> 00:27:29.059
They weren't there to support him.

00:27:29.059 --> 00:27:35.059
But what happened just a short while after Jesus had been resurrected?

00:27:35.059 --> 00:27:40.059
Well, it was amazing because some of those half-brothers

00:27:40.059 --> 00:27:46.059
found, along with Jesus' mother, with the disciples fervently praying.

00:27:46.059 --> 00:27:49.059
Can you imagine how Jesus must have felt?

00:27:49.059 --> 00:27:56.059
Can you imagine the joy he must have experienced to see them now beginning to express faith?

00:27:56.059 --> 00:27:59.059
Well, maybe you've had that experience too.

00:27:59.059 --> 00:28:03.059
Maybe one of your relatives, maybe your mate, one of your children,

00:28:03.059 --> 00:28:07.059
one of your siblings, has now come to serve Jehovah.

00:28:07.059 --> 00:28:09.059
How wonderful.

00:28:09.059 --> 00:28:12.059
Really, nothing could compare to it.

00:28:12.059 --> 00:28:18.059
Well, what was it that helped Jesus' half-brothers to go from being faithless

00:28:18.059 --> 00:28:20.059
to putting faith in him?

00:28:20.059 --> 00:28:24.059
And what can you and I learn from that example?

00:28:24.059 --> 00:28:26.059
Well, let's address that question.

00:28:26.059 --> 00:28:31.059
What was it that helped Jesus' brothers to acquire faith?

00:28:31.059 --> 00:28:34.059
Well, here's the number one thing.

00:28:34.059 --> 00:28:38.059
Jesus was patient with his relatives.

00:28:39.059 --> 00:28:45.059
Now, that's an important point because look at how Jesus was treated by his relatives.

00:28:45.059 --> 00:28:50.059
Would you look with me at Mark chapter 3 and verse 21?

00:28:50.059 --> 00:28:55.059
It says there, but when his relatives heard about it,

00:28:55.059 --> 00:29:02.059
they went out to seize him, for they were saying he has gone out of his mind.

00:29:02.059 --> 00:29:07.059
Jesus did not take offense, even though his relatives were trying to seize him,

00:29:07.059 --> 00:29:10.059
even though they said he had gone crazy.

00:29:10.059 --> 00:29:14.059
Have your relatives perhaps said some things like that to you?

00:29:14.059 --> 00:29:19.059
Jesus did not take offense, he was patient.

00:29:19.059 --> 00:29:24.059
Well, in fact, after his resurrection, look what Jesus did.

00:29:24.059 --> 00:29:29.059
Let's go to 1 Corinthians chapter 15 and let's read together verse 7.

00:29:29.059 --> 00:29:36.059
It says, after that, he appeared to James, then to all the apostles.

00:29:37.059 --> 00:29:41.059
Now, this is just a very small detail, but did you notice what it said?

00:29:41.059 --> 00:29:45.059
So Jesus appeared to James.

00:29:45.059 --> 00:29:50.059
Now, we don't know what Jesus said to James when he appeared to him,

00:29:50.059 --> 00:29:57.059
but the point is that Jesus made a special effort to appear to his half-brother James.

00:29:57.059 --> 00:30:03.059
Well, James must have deeply appreciated that special attention from Jesus.

00:30:03.059 --> 00:30:05.059
And why do we say that?

00:30:05.059 --> 00:30:13.059
Well, Jesus, excuse me, James, went on to become a respected elder in the congregation in Jerusalem.

00:30:13.059 --> 00:30:20.059
In fact, you may remember that in Acts chapter 15, when the apostles and older men gathered in Jerusalem

00:30:20.059 --> 00:30:28.059
to consider the matter about circumcision, it seems that James was the one who was presiding at that meeting.

00:30:28.059 --> 00:30:30.059
Well, what had happened?

00:30:30.059 --> 00:30:38.059
James had gone from being a faithless person to now being a pillar in the congregation.

00:30:38.059 --> 00:30:48.059
James and his other half-brother Jude both had the privilege of writing letters that were included in the Christian Greek scriptures.

00:30:48.059 --> 00:30:57.059
Well, now, in the following video, please take careful note of what helped a family member to be a person with faith.

